          <p>
Rake is a tool that was created out of necessity.
Being able to express and access dependency-based automation can be the difference between delivering code in hours instead of weeks.
Written by Jim Weirich, EdgeCase's Chief Scientist, Rake brings the power of this automation to Ruby.
But it is not specific to systems coded in Ruby - with Rake, developers can express dependency and automation for practically any system quickly and cleanly, putting power-user capabilites within everyone's reach.
          </p>
